Hi Team,  
 &nbsp; 
 Residential surcharges are simple to implement; they require one line of code per receiver and sender address. The address is not validated so if you are including them in your platform, I suggest
 you create a toggle box for the customers to say whether it is residential. 

 &nbsp; 
 I have attached the RTT documentation to this email it shows the inclusion of the Residential surcharge, you’ll be looking for the lines:

 &lt;residential&gt;RSD&lt;/residential&gt; after the delivery or receiver and &lt;residential&gt;RSP&lt;/residential&gt; for collection or sender. 
 &nbsp; 
 RSD= Delivery 
 RSP = Pickup 
 &nbsp; 
 Have a look at the documentation and I am happy to advise as needed. I also modified one of the request examples you send me you’ll be able to see the changes it isn’t much to add.



 Kind Regards, 
 &nbsp; 

Nick Evans | Customer Solutions Specialist | FedEx Express / TNT Australasia |
t: 0466 835 497 

